(49, 21, 'Formative Assessment 1: Problem Identification Matrix', NULL, 'Formative Assessment 1Problem Identification Matrix(by Romand Lansangan of Sec 47 Subsec 2)PROBLEM/ISSUE IN THE PHILIPPINE SOCIETYIMPACT TO DEVELOPMENTEXAMPLEFACTORS AFFECTING GLOBALIZATIONEXAMPLES1. Infrastructure and Urban Planning IssueInefficient governance, funding, and policy management negatively impact the economy\'s performance, slowing its growth.Daily traffic congestion results in economic losses of P3.5 billion, projected to reach P5.4 billion in 2035 (Cahiles-Magkilat, 2022). This threatens the country\'s vision of quality of life.Foreign direct investment (FDI) attraction and international competitiveness. “Transportation is a major contributor to the economy and a competitive fo', 0, '2023-12-11 20:47:22', '2023-12-11 21:36:03', '2023-12-11 20:47:22', '<p style=\'margin-right:0cm;margin-left:0cm;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;margin-top:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;font-size:11.0pt;text-align:center;\' id=\"isPasted\"><strong><span style=\'font-size:16px;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif;\'>Formative Assessment 1</span></strong></p><p style=\'margin-right:0cm;margin-left:0cm;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;margin-top:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;font-size:11.0pt;text-align:center;\'><strong><span style=\'font-size:16px;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif;\'>Problem Identification Matrix</span></strong></p><p style=\'margin-right:0cm;margin-left:0cm;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;margin-top:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;font-size:11.0pt;text-align:center;\'><span style=\'font-size:16px;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif;\'>(by Romand Lansangan of Sec 47 Subsec 2)</span></p><table border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" width=\"664\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse;border:none;\"><tbody><tr><td width=\"20%\" style=\"width:99.6pt;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt;background:#C5E0B3;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;height:34.85pt;\"><p style=\'margin-right:0cm;margin-left:0cm;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;margin-top:0cm;margin-bottom:0cm;font-size:11.0pt;text-align:center;line-height:normal;\'><span style=\'font-size:16px;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif;color:black;\'>PROBLEM/ISSUE IN THE PHILIPPINE SOCIETY</span></p></td><td width=\"20%\" style=\"width:99.6pt;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-left:  none;background:#C5E0B3;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;height:34.85pt;\"><p style=\'margin-right:0cm;margin-left:0cm;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;margin-top:0cm;margin-bottom:0cm;font-size:11.0pt;text-align:center;line-height:normal;\'><span style=\'font-size:16px;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif;color:black;\'>IMPACT TO DEVELOPMENT</span></p></td><td width=\"20%\" style=\"width:99.6pt;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-left:  none;background:#C5E0B3;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;height:34.85pt;\"><p style=\'margin-right:0cm;margin-left:0cm;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;margin-top:0cm;margin-bottom:0cm;font-size:11.0pt;text-align:center;line-height:normal;\'><span style=\'font-size:16px;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif;color:black;\'>EXAMPLE</span></p></td><td width=\"20%\" style=\"width:99.6pt;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-left:  none;background:#C5E0B3;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;height:34.85pt;\"><p style=\'margin-right:0cm;margin-left:0cm;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;margin-top:0cm;margin-bottom:0cm;font-size:11.0pt;text-align:center;line-height:normal;\'><span style=\'font-size:16px;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif;color:black;\'>FACTORS AFFECTING GLOBALIZATION</span></p></td><td width=\"20%\" style=\"width:99.9pt;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-left:  none;background:#C5E0B3;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;height:34.85pt;\"><p style=\'margin-right:0cm;margin-left:0cm;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;margin-top:0cm;margin-bottom:0cm;font-size:11.0pt;text-align:center;line-height:normal;\'><span style=\'font-size:16px;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif;color:black;\'>EXAMPLES</span></p></td></tr><tr><td width=\"20%\" style=\"width:99.6pt;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-top:  none;background:#E2EFD9;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;height:21.1pt;\"><p style=\"margin: 0cm; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt; text-align: center; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\'font-size:16px;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif;color:black;\'>1. Infrastructure and Urban Planning Issue</span></p></td><td width=\"20%\" style=\"width:99.6pt;border-top:none;border-left:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;height:21.1pt;\"><p style=\"margin: 0cm; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt; text-align: center; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\'font-size:16px;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif;\'>Inefficient governance, funding, and policy management negatively impact the economy&#39;s performance, slowing its growth.</span></p></td><td width=\"20%\" style=\"width:99.6pt;border-top:none;border-left:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;height:21.1pt;\"><p style=\"margin: 0cm; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt; text-align: center; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\'font-size:16px;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif;\'>Daily traffic congestion results in economic losses of P3.5 billion, projected to reach P5.4 billion in 2035 (Cahiles-Magkilat, 2022). This threatens the country&#39;s vision of quality of life.</span></p></td><td width=\"20%\" style=\"width:99.6pt;border-top:none;border-left:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;height:21.1pt;\"><p style=\"margin: 0cm; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt; text-align: center; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\'font-size:16px;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif;\'>Foreign direct investment (FDI) attraction and international competitiveness.</span></p></td><td width=\"20%\" style=\"width:99.9pt;border-top:none;border-left:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;height:21.1pt;\"><p style=\"margin: 0cm; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt; text-align: center; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\'font-size:16px;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif;\'>&nbsp;&ldquo;Transportation is a major contributor to the economy and a competitive force in business&rdquo; (The Critical Role of Transportation in Business and the Economy, 2014). Investors are deterred by inefficiencies in infrastructure, as this can lead to higher operational costs.&nbsp;</span></p></td></tr><tr><td width=\"20%\" style=\"width:99.6pt;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-top:  none;background:#E2EFD9;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;height:21.1pt;\"><p style=\"margin: 0cm; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt; text-align: center; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\'font-size:16px;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif;color:black;\'>2. Identity Politics</span></p></td><td width=\"20%\" style=\"width:99.6pt;border-top:none;border-left:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;height:21.1pt;\"><p style=\"margin: 0cm; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt; text-align: center; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\'font-size:16px;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif;\'>Focusing on the promoter rather than the policy divides society, impeding progress. Finding common ground based on ideas is easier than doing so based on personalities. This hinders national development as it fails to maximize the potential and collaboration of its people.</span></p></td><td width=\"20%\" style=\"width:99.6pt;border-top:none;border-left:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;height:21.1pt;\"><p style=\"margin: 0cm; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt; text-align: center; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\'font-size:16px;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif;\'>The political landscape is divided into factions such as &#39;Dilawan&#39;, DDS, or Marcos loyalists. This division often leads to &#39;Groupthink,&#39; where consensus overrides rationality, potentially skewing or censoring necessary discussions (Kenton, 2022).</span></p></td><td width=\"20%\" style=\"width:99.6pt;border-top:none;border-left:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;height:21.1pt;\"><p style=\"margin: 0cm; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt; text-align: center; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\'font-size:16px;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif;\'>Global perception and international diplomatic relationships.</span></p></td><td width=\"20%\" style=\"width:99.9pt;border-top:none;border-left:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;height:21.1pt;\"><p style=\"margin: 0cm; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt; text-align: center; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\'font-size:16px;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif;\'>Persistent internal divisions, especially when they are tied to historical narratives, can influence how the Philippines negotiates with other countries or is perceived by potential investors. Foreign relations can be affected if global leaders or diplomats align with one faction over another.</span></p></td></tr><tr><td width=\"20%\" style=\"width:99.6pt;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-top:  none;background:#E2EFD9;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;height:21.1pt;\"><p style=\"margin: 0cm; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt; text-align: center; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\'font-size:16px;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif;color:black;\'>3. Unemployment Rate</span></p></td><td width=\"20%\" style=\"width:99.6pt;border-top:none;border-left:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;height:21.1pt;\"><p style=\"margin: 0cm; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt; text-align: center; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\'font-size:16px;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif;\'>Unemployment influences both economic and social facets of a nation&#39;s development. Economically, it leads to reduced purchasing power, a drop in GDP, diminished national output, and fiscal challenges like budget deficits. Socially, it exacerbates issues like crime and income inequality.</span></p></td><td width=\"20%\" style=\"width:99.6pt;border-top:none;border-left:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;height:21.1pt;\"><p style=\"margin: 0cm; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt; text-align: center; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\'font-size:16px;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif;\'>In the Philippines, despite promising economic projections for 2030, the nation contends with pronounced social challenges. The 2009 Gini coefficient of 43.0 reflects stark income inequality, and there&#39;s a tangible link between unemployment and crime rates (as cited in Impacts, n.d.).</span></p></td><td width=\"20%\" style=\"width:99.6pt;border-top:none;border-left:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;height:21.1pt;\"><p style=\"margin: 0cm; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt; text-align: center; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\'font-size:16px;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif;\'>Dependency on overseas employment and brain drain</span></p></td><td width=\"20%\" style=\"width:99.9pt;border-top:none;border-left:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;height:21.1pt;\"><p style=\"margin: 0cm; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt; text-align: center; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\'font-size:16px;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif;\'>High unemployment in the Philippines has historically driven many Filipinos abroad for jobs. While this boosts the economy through remittances, it also causes a brain drain, depriving the local industry of skilled labor. Both phenomena (unemployment and brain drain) signify the underutilization of human resources, with qualified personnel migrating overseas (Ray, 1971).</span></p></td></tr><tr><td width=\"20%\" style=\"width:99.6pt;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-top:  none;background:#E2EFD9;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;height:20.2pt;\"><p style=\"margin: 0cm; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt; text-align: center; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\'font-size:16px;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif;color:black;\'>4. Geological location</span></p></td><td width=\"20%\" style=\"width:99.6pt;border-top:none;border-left:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;height:20.2pt;\"><p style=\"margin: 0cm; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt; text-align: center; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\'font-size:16px;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif;\'>The Philippine archipelago&#39;s diverse and challenging geography hinders development due to frequent natural disasters and the isolation of some areas from the central government. This dispersed nature makes national unity difficult.</span></p></td><td width=\"20%\" style=\"width:99.6pt;border-top:none;border-left:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;height:20.2pt;\"><p style=\"margin: 0cm; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt; text-align: center; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\'font-size:16px;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif;\'>Areas lacking infrastructure such as roads and electricity feel isolated. Making it harder for the government to provide basic needs such as health, livelihood, and education. Relief distribution after natural calamities is also a challenge due to these geographic barriers (Philippines Geography Has Advantages as Well as Disadvantages, n.d.).</span></p></td><td width=\"20%\" style=\"width:99.6pt;border-top:none;border-left:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;height:20.2pt;\"><p style=\"margin: 0cm; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt; text-align: center; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\'font-size:16px;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif;\'>Dependency on international aid and vulnerability to global environmental changes.</span></p></td><td width=\"20%\" style=\"width:99.9pt;border-top:none;border-left:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;height:20.2pt;\"><p style=\"margin: 0cm; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt; text-align: center; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\'font-size:16px;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif;\'>The Philippines&#39; vulnerability to natural disasters often necessitates international relief and aid. Additionally, global phenomena like climate change can intensify the frequency and severity of these natural disasters (United States Geological Survey, 2020).</span></p></td></tr><tr><td width=\"20%\" style=\"width:99.6pt;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-top:  none;background:#E2EFD9;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;height:21.1pt;\"><p style=\"margin: 0cm; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt; text-align: center; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\'font-size:16px;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif;color:black;\'>5. Culture of smallness</span></p></td><td width=\"20%\" style=\"width:99.6pt;border-top:none;border-left:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;height:21.1pt;\"><p style=\"margin: 0cm; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt; text-align: center; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\'font-size:16px;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif;\'>The Philippine mindset, historically and culturally, tends to favor the small, the immediate, and the familiar over large ventures and bold risks. This &#39;culture of smallness&#39; has led to a preference for short-term gains and immediate results, often at the expense of long-term, sustained efforts and larger visions. Joaquin&#39;s observation that Filipinos often opt for the &#39;tingi&#39; or retailing in tiny quantities showcases the tendency to think and act small. This can hinder the potential for expansive growth, innovation, and broad societal progress.</span></p></td><td width=\"20%\" style=\"width:99.6pt;border-top:none;border-left:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;height:21.1pt;\"><p style=\"margin: 0cm; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt; text-align: center; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\'font-size:16px;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif;\'>Nick Joaquin illustrates this cultural trait through various vignettes: the sale of a single stick of cigarette or a single banana, the barangay as the primary societal unit, and the local sari-sari store that deals in minute transactions. Furthermore, Joaquin contrasts the Filipino&#39;s small ventures like the inter-island migrations on rowboats to the more audacious ventures of other cultures, like the voyage across oceans to an unknown world. This lack of appetite for risk and grand vision, he argues, has stifled Philippine growth and progress in the larger scheme of things (<em>A Heritage of Smallness by Nick Joaquin</em>, 2011)</span></p></td><td width=\"20%\" style=\"width:99.6pt;border-top:none;border-left:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;height:21.1pt;\"><p style=\"margin: 0cm; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt; text-align: center; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\'font-size:16px;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif;\'>Reluctance to engage in international scale projects and ventures, preference for local over global.</span></p></td><td width=\"20%\" style=\"width:99.9pt;border-top:none;border-left:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;height:21.1pt;\"><p style=\"margin: 0cm; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt; text-align: center; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\'font-size:16px;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif;\'>A culture of smallness might deter Philippine businesses from expanding internationally or forming collaborations with foreign entities. This can limit the country&#39;s presence in the global market and hinder the potential for international partnerships.</span></p></td></tr><tr><td width=\"100%\" colspan=\"5\" style=\"width:498.3pt;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-top:none;background:#C5E0B3;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;height:21.1pt;\"><p style=\'margin-right:0cm;margin-left:0cm;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;margin-top:0cm;margin-bottom:0cm;font-size:11.0pt;text-align:center;line-height:normal;\'><span style=\'font-size:16px;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif;color:black;\'>SYNTHESIS</span></p></td></tr><tr><td width=\"100%\" colspan=\"5\" style=\"width:498.3pt;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-top:none;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;height:63.35pt;\"><p style=\"margin: 0cm; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt; text-align: center; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\'font-size:16px;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif;\'>&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin: 0cm; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt; text-align: center; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\'font-size:16px;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif;\'>The Philippines faces multifaceted challenges that impact its developmental trajectory&mdash;in the midst of heightened globalization. Infrastructure meagerness, such as traffic congestion, impedes economic growth and hinders Foreign Direct Investment due to operational inefficiencies. Identity politics hinder national unity, with factions like &#39;Dilawan&#39; and &#39;DDS&#39; overshadowing policy considerations and potentially skewing diplomatic perceptions. The nation grapples with high unemployment, prompting many to seek opportunities abroad, boosting remittances but also causing a brain drain. The archipelago&#39;s geography complicates development, with its vulnerability to natural disasters necessitating international aid and making it susceptible to global environmental shifts&mdash;amplified by climate change. Lastly, the &#39;culture of smallness&#39; prioritizes immediate over long-term gains, suppressing expansive growth and limiting international business ventures. Each issue offers insights into the interplay of local concerns with the broader forces of globalization.</span></p></td></tr><tr><td width=\"100%\" colspan=\"5\" style=\"width:498.3pt;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-top:none;background:#C5E0B3;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;height:21.1pt;\"><p style=\'margin-right:0cm;margin-left:0cm;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;margin-top:0cm;margin-bottom:0cm;font-size:11.0pt;text-align:center;line-height:normal;\'><span style=\'font-size:16px;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif;color:black;\'>REFLECTION</span></p></td></tr><tr><td width=\"100%\" colspan=\"5\" style=\"width:498.3pt;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt;border-top:none;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;height:62.4pt;\"><p style=\"margin: 0cm; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt; text-align: center; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\'font-size:16px;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif;\'>&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin: 0cm; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt; text-align: center; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\'font-size:16px;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif;\'>After thoroughly considering a wide range of potential problems and verifying them through comprehensive research, I&#39;ve come to understand the intricate complexities of achieving success as a nation, particularly in the rising tide of globalization. Various facets of human society, regardless of their perceived insignificance or disconnect, whether in the realms of social science, economy, policy, or culture, seem to have a more significant impact than initially evident. The challenges appear to be deeply rooted in both the cultural fabric of the people and the policies promoted by those in power, as well as in the broader systemic framework. Although I&#39;ve proposed rationally conceivable solutions, I remain skeptical about the easiness of their implementation. Crafting specific policies without jeopardizing other aspects of the Philippine government and society will be challenging. Nevertheless, this experience has introduced me to more complexities to ponder. However, this isn&#39;t entirely discouraging; true triumph often emerges from the determination to overcome seemingly impossible challenges.</span></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0cm 36pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt; text-align: center; text-indent: -36pt; line-height: 200%;\"><em>&nbsp;</em></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em><span style=\'font-size:16px;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif;\'><br>&nbsp;</span></em></p><p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt; text-align: center;\"><em><span style=\'font-size:16px;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif;\'>&nbsp;</span></em></p><p style=\'margin-right:0cm;margin-left:36.0pt;font-size:16px;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;margin-top:0cm;margin-bottom:0cm;font-size:11.0pt;text-align:center;text-indent:-36.0pt;line-height:200%;\'><strong>REFERENCES</strong></p><p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0cm 36pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt; text-align: center; text-indent: -36pt; line-height: 200%;\"><em>A Heritage of Smallness by Nick Joaquin</em>. (2011, May 29). Tumblr. https://theurbanhistorian.tumblr.com/post/5966825494/a-heritage-of-a-by-nick-joaquin</p><p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0cm 36pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt; text-align: center; text-indent: -36pt; line-height: 200%;\">Cahiles-Magkilat, B. (2022, May 10). <em>PCCI laments deteriorating Manila traffic condition</em>. Manila Bulletin. https://mb.com.ph/2022/05/09/pcci-laments-deteriorating-manila-traffic-condition/</p><p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0cm 36pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt; text-align: center; text-indent: -36pt; line-height: 200%;\">Corcuera, J. (2020, November 23). The world is not black and white. <em>DailyGuardian</em>. https://dailyguardian.com.ph/the-world-is-not-black-and-white/</p><p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0cm 36pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt; text-align: center; text-indent: -36pt; line-height: 200%;\"><em>Impacts</em>. (n.d.). Unemployment in the Philippines. http://econsilp2014.weebly.com/impacts.html#:~:text=Unemployment%20can%20result%20in%20debt,revenue%20and%20increased%20welfare%20spending.</p><p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0cm 36pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt; text-align: center; text-indent: -36pt; line-height: 200%;\">Kenton, W. (2022). What is groupthink? Definition, characteristics, and causes. <em>Investopedia</em>. https://www.investopedia.com/terms/g/groupthink.asp#:~:text=Groupthink%20is%20a%20phenomenon%20that,of%20a%20group%20of%20people.</p><p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0cm 36pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt; text-align: center; text-indent: -36pt; line-height: 200%;\">Palanca-Tan, R. (2021, October). <em>Income and Happiness: a Philippine context</em>. Archīum Ateneo. https://archium.ateneo.edu/economics-faculty-pubs/148/#:~:text=The%20study%20provides%20empirical%20evidence,a%20scale%20of%200%E2%80%9310.</p><p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0cm 36pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt; text-align: center; text-indent: -36pt; line-height: 200%;\"><em>Philippines Geography Has Advantages As Well As Disadvantages</em>. (n.d.). Expersculumn.com. https://travelandculture.expertscolumn.com/advantage-and-disadvantage-philippines-geographical-location</p><p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0cm 36pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt; text-align: center; text-indent: -36pt; line-height: 200%;\">Ray, K. (1971). Unemployment and Brain Drain. <em>Economic and Political Weekly</em>, <em>6</em>(39), 2059. http://www.jstor.org/stable/4382568</p><p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0cm 36pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt; text-align: center; text-indent: -36pt; line-height: 200%;\">United States Geological Survey. (2020, June 2). <em>How can climate change affect natural disasters?</em> U.S. Geological Survey. https://www.usgs.gov/faqs/how-can-climate-change-affect-natural-disasters#:~:text=With%20increasing%20global%20surface%20temperatures,more%20powerful%20storms%20to%20develop.</p><p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt; text-align: center;\"><span style=\'font-size:16px;line-height:107%;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif;color:#343332;\'>&nbsp;</span></p>', 'private'),
(50, 21, 'FA1: Questions', NULL, 'Audience: The general population. Our primary goal is to resonate with our primary supporters (DDS) while also appealing to a broader audience. How can we effectively cater to both groups, recognizing their possible differences and similarities?Context: We\'re amidst a presidential campaign, and it\'s worth noting that in 2016 the Philippines ranked 17th out of 144 countries in the Global Gender Report by the World Economic Forum. Given this ranking, how can we address gender issues responsibly, knowing that it is a pivotal topic for the country?Purpose: Our objective is to highlight our candidness, our strong leadership traits, and our unique sense of humor. Given the gravity of discussing th', 0, '2023-12-11 22:00:26', NULL, '2023-12-11 22:00:26', '<p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;\' id=\"isPasted\"><strong><span style=\'font-size:16px;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif;\'>Audience</span></strong><span style=\'font-size:16px;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif;\'>: The general population. Our primary goal is to resonate with our primary supporters (DDS) while also appealing to a broader audience. How can we effectively cater to both groups, recognizing their possible differences and similarities?</span></p><p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;\'><strong><span style=\'font-size:16px;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif;\'>Context</span></strong><span style=\'font-size:16px;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif;\'>: We&#39;re amidst a presidential campaign, and it&#39;s worth noting that in 2016 the Philippines ranked 17th out of 144 countries in the Global Gender Report by the World Economic Forum. Given this ranking, how can we address gender issues responsibly, knowing that it is a pivotal topic for the country?</span></p><p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;\'><strong><span style=\'font-size:16px;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif;\'>Purpose</span></strong><span style=\'font-size:16px;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif;\'>: Our objective is to highlight our candidness, our strong leadership traits, and our unique sense of humor. Given the gravity of discussing the incident with the Australian woman, how can we approach it without compromising ethics and also maintaining the essence of our brand?</span></p><p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;\'><strong><span style=\'font-size:16px;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif;\'>Addressing the Incident</span></strong><span style=\'font-size:16px;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif;\'>: How can we narrate the story about the raped Australian woman in a way that shows compassion and respect towards the victim, and also sheds light on our leadership skills during that difficult time?</span></p><p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;\'><strong><span style=\'font-size:16px;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif;\'>On Using Jokes:</span></strong></p><p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\'font-size:16px;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif;\'>Should we maintain humor when talking about such a sensitive topic?</span></p><p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\'font-size:16px;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif;\'>If we decide to incorporate humor, how can we ensure its respectful and does not trivialize serious issues?</span></p><p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\'font-size:16px;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif;\'>Can we think of any other anecdotes or events that can illustrate our edgy sense of humor without risking offense?</span></p><p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;\'><strong><span style=\'font-size:16px;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif;\'>Using Profanity and Threats:</span></strong></p><p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\'font-size:16px;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif;\'>How does the use of strong language align with our brand?</span></p><p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\'font-size:16px;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif;\'>Do death threats emphasize our strong leadership, or do they alienate a portion of our audience?</span></p><p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\'font-size:16px;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif;\'>Given the reactions in the past, should we moderate our language or stay consistent with our unfiltered approach? How might this decision affect our broader appeal?</span></p><p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;\'><strong><span style=\'font-size:16px;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif;\'>Final Considerations:</span></strong></p><p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\'font-size:16px;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif;\'>Are there other events from our past that we can highlight to emphasize our leadership skills and our commitment to the Filipino people?</span></p><p style=\'margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0cm;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;\'><span style=\'font-size:16px;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",serif;\'>How can we use this speech as an opportunity to bridge any divides and resonate with as many Filipinos as possible?</span></p>', 'public'),
