e;white-space:pre-wrap;\">&nbsp;denotes the acceleration of the object which is constant in magnitude and direction. &nbsp;</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.295;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0.15pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Garamond,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">&nbsp;</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.295;margin-left: 36.9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><br></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3150000000000002;margin-left: 0.5pt;text-indent: 18pt;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0.2pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Garamond,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">&nbsp;Consider a block placed on a smooth inclined plane as shown in Figure 4-1. The acceleration due to gravity points directly downward but can be decomposed into its components that are perpendicular and parallel to the plane. Hence, as the block moves downward the inclined plane, its acceleration is simply the component of the acceleration due to gravity parallel to the plane, i.e.&nbsp;</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.295;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0.05pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Garamond,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">&nbsp;</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.295;margin-left: 0.5pt;margin-right: 4.65pt;text-indent: 18pt;text-align: center;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:\'Cambria Math\',serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">𝑎 = 𝑔 𝑠𝑖𝑛𝜃 &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;(2) &nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Garamond,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">&nbsp;</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.295;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Garamond,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">&nbsp;</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.295;margin-left: -0.25pt;text-indent: 18pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Garamond,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Experimental Procedure&nbsp;</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.295;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2.35pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Garamond,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">&nbsp;</span></p><h2 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.295;margin-left: -0.25pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2.3pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Garamond,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">A.</span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Garamond,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Computer Setup&nbsp;</span></h2><ol style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px;\"><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal;font-size:11pt;font-family:Garamond,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;margin-left: -4.6pt;\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3150000000000002;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2.05pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Garamond,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Connect the interface to the computer and turn it on. The switch is in front panel of the interface.&nbsp;</span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal;font-size:11pt;font-family:Garamond,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;margin-left: -4.6pt;\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.28;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2.5pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Garamond,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Plug in the photogate&rsquo;s sensor to the Digital Input 1 of the interface. &nbsp;</span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal;font-size:11pt;font-family:Garamond,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;margin-left: -4.6pt;\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3150000000000002;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2.05pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Garamond,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Launch the Capstone software in the computer to create a new experiment file.&nbsp;</span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal;font-size:11pt;font-family:Garamond,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;margin-left: -4.6pt;\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.28;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2.5pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Garamond,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Under the Tools palette (left side of the window), click the &ldquo;Hardware Setup.&rdquo; Click the Digital Input 1 port and from the drop-down list, select &ldquo;Picket Fence.&rdquo;&nbsp;</span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal;font-size:11pt;font-family:Garamond,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;margin-left: -4.6pt;\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3150000000000002;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0.2pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Garamond,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;tex