ng&rdquo; refers to the distance between two consecutive opaque bands of the picket fence to be used (Figure 4-2). By default, it is set to 0.05m in the Capstone software. To confirm the flag spacing, use a ruler to measure it before proceeding to the experiment.&nbsp;</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.295;margin-left: 0.5pt;margin-right: -0.4pt;text-indent: 18pt;text-align: right;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Garamond,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">under the display palette at the right side of the window. On the&nbsp;</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.28;margin-left: 28.8pt;text-indent: 17.999999999999996pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2.5pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Garamond,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">displayed graph, set the y-axis to &ldquo;Speed (m/s)&rdquo; and the x-axis to &ldquo;Time (s)&rdquo; by clicking the &lt;Select Measurement&gt; button. &nbsp;</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3150000000000002;margin-left: 13.4pt;text-indent: -14.15pt;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0.2pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.15pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Garamond,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">7.</span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Garamond,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">To add another plot area, double click again the graph icon. Set the y-axis to &ldquo;Acceleration (m/s</span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Garamond,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"font-size:0.6em;vertical-align:super;\">2</span></span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Garamond,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">)&rdquo; and the x-axis to &ldquo;Time (s).&rdquo;&nbsp;</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.295;margin-left: 28.3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2.35pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Garamond,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">&nbsp;</span></p><h2 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.295;margin-left: -0.25pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:3.2pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Garamond,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">B.</span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Garamond,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Equipment Setup&nbsp;</span></h2><ol style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px;\"><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal;font-size:11pt;font-family:Garamond,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;margin-left: -4.6pt;\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3150000000000002;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:1.8pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Garamond,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Place the linear track on a horizontal surface. Measure its length and denote it as&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:\'Cambria Math\',serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">𝐿</span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Garamond,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">.&nbsp;</span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal;font-size:11pt;font-family:Garamond,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;margin-left: -4.6pt;\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3150000000000002;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:3pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Garamond,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">If not installed, mount a bumper on the open end of the track.&nbsp;</span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal;font-size:11pt;font-family:Garamond,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;margin-left: -4.6pt;\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3150000000000002;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:1.65pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Garamond,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Raise one end of the track by 10cm using a support rod. Denote this height as&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:\'Cambria Math\',serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">ℎ</span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Garamond,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">. &nbsp;</span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal;font-size:11pt;font-family:Garamond,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;margin-left: -4.6pt;\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3150000000000002;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2.05pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Garamond,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Put the picket fence on top of the cart.&nbsp;</span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal;font-size:11pt;font-family:Garamond,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;margin-left: -4.6pt;\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3150000000000002;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0.2pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Garamond,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Mount the photogate sensor above the track. Its height should be enough to allow the cart with the picket fence to pass through it. &nbsp;</span></p></li></ol><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3150000000000002;margin-left: 28.8pt;text-indent: 17.999999999999996pt;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0.2pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Garamond,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:underline;-webkit-text-decoration-skip:none;text-decoration-skip-ink:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Note:</span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Garamond,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">&nbsp;Make sure the sensor&rsquo;s beam is hitting the series of bands of the picket fence. To check, move the cart (with picket fence) through the sensor. The light on the sensor turns on when the photogate beam is blocked and turns off otherwise. &nbsp;</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.295;margin-left: 28.3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Garamond,serif